extremeSystem.name: extremeSystem
extremeSystem.description: Extreme System objects: objects common to all platforms

SlotType.name: SlotType
SlotType.description: The type of the slot. It is used both for the configured as well as the inserted slot types.

PowerValue.name: PowerValue
PowerValue.description: The input power value of the switch.

UnitMultiplier.name: UnitMultiplier
UnitMultiplier.description: The Unit Multiplier is an integer value that represents the IEEE 61850 Annex A units multiplier associated with the integer units used to measure the power or energy. For example, when used with pmPowerUnitMultiplier, -3 represents 10^-3 or milliwatts.
UnitMultiplier.reference: The International System of Units (SI), National Institute of Standards and Technology, Spec. Publ. 330, August 1991.

extremeSaveConfiguration.name: extremeSaveConfiguration
extremeSaveConfiguration.description: When this object is set, the device will copy the contents of the configuration database to a buffer and save it to the persistant store specified by the value of the object. The save is performed asynchronously, and the snmp agent will continue to respond to both gets and sets while the save is taking place. A network management application may use the extremeSaveStatus object to determine when the asynchronous save operation has completed.

extremeSaveStatus.name: extremeSaveStatus
extremeSaveStatus.description: This object will return the status of a save operation invoked by setting the extremeSaveConfiguration object. A network management application can read this object to determine that a save operation has completed.

extremeCurrentConfigInUse.name: extremeCurrentConfigInUse
extremeCurrentConfigInUse.description: Shows which NVRAM configuration store was used at last boot.

extremeConfigToUseOnReboot.name: extremeConfigToUseOnReboot
extremeConfigToUseOnReboot.description: Controls which NVRAM configuration store will be used on next reboot.

extremeSaveConfigurationFileName.name: extremeSaveConfigurationFileName
extremeSaveConfigurationFileName.description: This object is set, along the object extremSaveConfiguration option with value 5.This object indicates the file name to be used while saving the file. On reading it returns the current selected config.

extremeUseOnRebootFileName.name: extremeUseOnRebootFileName
extremeUseOnRebootFileName.description: This object is set, along the object extremeConfigToUseOnReboot option with value 3.This object indicates the file name to be used while saving the file

extremeOverTemperatureAlarm.name: extremeOverTemperatureAlarm
extremeOverTemperatureAlarm.description: Alarm status of overtemperature sensor in device enclosure.

extremeCurrentTemperature.name: extremeCurrentTemperature
extremeCurrentTemperature.description: Current temperature in degrees celcius measured inside device enclosure.

extremeFanStatusTable.name: extremeFanStatusTable
extremeFanStatusTable.description: Table of operational status of all internal cooling fans.

extremeFanStatusEntry.name: extremeFanStatusEntry
extremeFanStatusEntry.description: Entry in table of all internal cooling fans.

extremeFanNumber.name: extremeFanNumber
extremeFanNumber.description: Identifier of cooling fan, numbered from the front and/or left side of device.

extremeFanOperational.name: extremeFanOperational
extremeFanOperational.description: Operational status of a cooling fan.

extremeFanEntPhysicalIndex.name: extremeFanEntPhysicalIndex
extremeFanEntPhysicalIndex.description: The entity index for this fan entity in the entityPhysicalTable table of the entity MIB.

extremeFanSpeed.name: extremeFanSpeed
extremeFanSpeed.description: The speed (RPM) of a cooling fan in the fantray.

extremePrimaryPowerOperational.name: extremePrimaryPowerOperational
extremePrimaryPowerOperational.description: Operational status of internal power supply of a device.

extremeRedundantPowerStatus.name: extremeRedundantPowerStatus
extremeRedundantPowerStatus.description: Operational status of an external redundant power supply to a device.

extremeRedundantPowerAlarm.name: extremeRedundantPowerAlarm
extremeRedundantPowerAlarm.description: Alarm state of an external redundant power supply to a device. Alarm state indicates either fan failure or overtemperature condition.

extremePrimarySoftwareRev.name: extremePrimarySoftwareRev
extremePrimarySoftwareRev.description: The software revision of the primary image stored in this device. This string will have a zero length if the revision is unknown, invalid or not present. This will also be reported in RMON2 probeSoftwareRev if this is the software image currently running in the device.

extremeSecondarySoftwareRev.name: extremeSecondarySoftwareRev
extremeSecondarySoftwareRev.description: The software revision of the secondary image stored in this device. This string will have a zero length if the revision is unknown, invalid or not present. This will also be reported in RMON2 probeSoftwareRev if this is the software image currently running in the device.

extremeImageToUseOnReboot.name: extremeImageToUseOnReboot
extremeImageToUseOnReboot.description: Controls which image will be used on next reboot.

extremeSystemID.name: extremeSystemID
extremeSystemID.description: This represents the System ID of the Summit Switch.

extremeSystemBoardID.name: extremeSystemBoardID
extremeSystemBoardID.description: This represents the Board ID of the Summit Switch.

extremeSystemLeftBoardID.name: extremeSystemLeftBoardID
extremeSystemLeftBoardID.description: This represents the Left Board ID of the Summit Switch.

extremeSystemRightBoardID.name: extremeSystemRightBoardID
extremeSystemRightBoardID.description: This represents the Right Board ID of the Summit Switch.

extremeInputPowerVoltage.name: extremeInputPowerVoltage
extremeInputPowerVoltage.description: The input power voltage at which the system is currently operating.

extremePowerStatus.name: extremePowerStatus
extremePowerStatus.description: Operational status of the power supply to a device.

extremePowerAlarm.name: extremePowerAlarm
extremePowerAlarm.description: Alarm state of the power supply to a device. Alarm state indicates either fan failure or overtemperature condition.

extremeRmonEnable.name: extremeRmonEnable
extremeRmonEnable.description: Setting this to true will cause the agent to start collecting RMON statistics.

extremeBootROMVersion.name: extremeBootROMVersion
extremeBootROMVersion.description: The software revision of the bootrom on the device. This string will have a zero length if the revision is unknown or invalid.

extremeDot1dTpFdbTableEnable.name: extremeDot1dTpFdbTableEnable
extremeDot1dTpFdbTableEnable.description: Setting this to true will cause GetNext operations on the dot1dTpFdbTable to be allowed. Note that Get operations are always allowed.

extremePowerSupplyTable.name: extremePowerSupplyTable
extremePowerSupplyTable.description: Table of status of all power supplies in the system.

extremePowerSupplyEntry.name: extremePowerSupplyEntry
extremePowerSupplyEntry.description: An entry indicating the status of a specific power supply.

extremePowerSupplyInputVoltage.name: extremePowerSupplyInputVoltage
extremePowerSupplyInputVoltage.description: Input voltage of the power supply

extremePowerSupplySerialNumber.name: extremePowerSupplySerialNumber
extremePowerSupplySerialNumber.description: The serial number of the power supply unit.

extremePowerSupplyEntPhysicalIndex.name: extremePowerSupplyEntPhysicalIndex
extremePowerSupplyEntPhysicalIndex.description: The entity index for this psu entity in the entityPhysicalTable of the entity MIB.

extremePowerSupplyFan1Speed.name: extremePowerSupplyFan1Speed
extremePowerSupplyFan1Speed.description: The speed (RPM) of Fan-1 in the power supply unit.

extremePowerSupplyFan2Speed.name: extremePowerSupplyFan2Speed
extremePowerSupplyFan2Speed.description: The speed (RPM) of Fan-2 in the power supply unit.

extremePowerSupplySource.name: extremePowerSupplySource
extremePowerSupplySource.description: The power supply unit input source.

extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsage.name: extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsage
extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsage.description: Input power usage for the given psu slot. The value 0 in this field indicate the power usage is not supported or read failure.

extremePowerMonSupplyNumOutput.name: extremePowerMonSupplyNumOutput
extremePowerMonSupplyNumOutput.description: Number of output sensors in the power supply unit

extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsageUnitMul.name: extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsageUnitMultiplier
extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsageUnitMul.description: The magnitude of watts for the usage value in extremePowerSupplyInputPowerUsage.

extremeCpuAggregateUtilization.name: extremeCpuAggregateUtilization
extremeCpuAggregateUtilization.description: The aggregate CPU utilization since the time the start started executing.

extremeCpuTask2Table.name: extremeCpuTask2Table
extremeCpuTask2Table.description: Table of CPU tasks that are active.

extremeCpuTask2Entry.name: extremeCpuTask2Entry
extremeCpuTask2Entry.description: An entry in table of describes a single task.

extremeCpuTask2CpuId.name: extremeCpuTask2CpuId
extremeCpuTask2CpuId.description: CPU on which this task last executed or is executing. The primary CPU has a value of 1.

extremeCpuTask2Name.name: extremeCpuTask2Name
extremeCpuTask2Name.description: Name associated with the reported task id.

extremeCpuTask2Id.name: extremeCpuTask2Id
extremeCpuTask2Id.description: Task identifier assigned by the operating system when this task is spawned.

extremeCpuTask2Pc.name: extremeCpuTask2Pc
extremeCpuTask2Pc.description: The value of the program counter for this task. It indicates the address of the next instruction that would be executed once the operating system resumes this task.

extremeCpuTask2Status.name: extremeCpuTask2Status
extremeCpuTask2Status.description: The current status of the task as reported by the operating system.

extremeCpuTask2Utilization.name: extremeCpuTask2Utilization
extremeCpuTask2Utilization.description: The current CPU utilization by this task. This is the utilization when the task last executed.

extremeCpuTask2MaxUtilization.name: extremeCpuTask2MaxUtilization
extremeCpuTask2MaxUtilization.description: The maximum CPU utilization by this task since the time the start started executing. This value may be cleared.

extremeAuthFailSrcAddr.name: extremeAuthFailSrcAddr
extremeAuthFailSrcAddr.description: The IP address of the originator of the bad SNMP request that caused the generation of an authentication failure trap.

extremeImageBooted.name: extremeImageBooted
extremeImageBooted.description: The image with which the switch was last booted, using which it is currently running.

extremeMsmFailoverCause.name: extremeMsmFailoverCause
extremeMsmFailoverCause.description: The cause of the last MSM failover. never(1) means an MSM Failover has not occurred since the last reboot. admin(2) means the failover was initiated by the user. exception(3) means the former master MSM encountered a software exception condition. removal(4) means the master MSM was physically removed from the chassis. hwFailure(5) means a diagnostic failure was detected in the master MSM. watchdog(6) means that the master MSM hardware watchdog timer expired. keepalive(7) means the master MSM failed to respond to slave keepalive requests. The MSM failover will have been hitless only in the admin(2) and exception(3) cases

extremeImageTable.name: extremeImageTable
extremeImageTable.description: A table containing information about each software image.

extremeImageEntry.name: extremeImageEntry
extremeImageEntry.description: A table entry containing information about each software image.

extremeImageNumber.name: extremeImageNumber
extremeImageNumber.description: A unique integer identifying the particular software image.

extremeTechnologyReleaseNumber.name: extremeTechnologyReleaseNumber
extremeTechnologyReleaseNumber.description: The Technology Release version. This value is zero for all but TR releases.

extremeSustainingReleaseNumber.name: extremeSustainingReleaseNumber
extremeSustainingReleaseNumber.description: The Sustaining Release number for the ExtremeWare version.

extremeBranchRevisionNumber.name: extremeBranchRevisionNumber
extremeBranchRevisionNumber.description: The incremental build on specified branch.

extremeImageType.name: extremeImageType
extremeImageType.description: The branch type from which the image was built.

extremeImageDescription.name: extremeImageDescription
extremeImageDescription.description: A unique string that can be used to identify the specific patch, technology, or development branch release.

extremeImageSecurity.name: extremeImageSecurity
extremeImageSecurity.description: Indicates whether image was built with ssh. This object is deprecated, the ssh capability can be obtained from the extremeImageSshCapability of the ImageFeatureTable

extremeImageFeatureTable.name: extremeImageFeatureTable
extremeImageFeatureTable.description: A table containing information about the software features.

extremeImageFeatureEntry.name: extremeImageFeatureEntry
extremeImageFeatureEntry.description: A table entry containing information about software features.

extremeImageFeatureNumber.name: extremeImageFeatureNumber
extremeImageFeatureNumber.description: A unique integer identifying the particular software image.

extremeImageSshCapability.name: extremeImageSshCapability
extremeImageSshCapability.description: Indicates whether image has ssh capability.

extremeImageUAACapability.name: extremeImageUAACapability
extremeImageUAACapability.description: Indicates whether image has Wireless(UAA) components.

extremeSystemPowerState.name: extremeSystemPowerState
extremeSystemPowerState.description: The current state of power available.

extremeBootTime.name: extremeBootTime
extremeBootTime.description: The boot time expressed in standard time_t value. When interpreted as an absolute time value, it represents the number of seconds elapsed since 00:00:00 on January 1, 1970, Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)

extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerTable.name: extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerTable
extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerTable.description: The output power supply table per power supply unit.

extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerEntry.name: extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerEntry
extremePowerSupplyOutputPowerEntry.description: An entry in the power supply output table.

extremePowerSupplyOutputVoltage.name: extremePowerSupplyOutputVoltage
extremePowerSupplyOutputVoltage.description: Output voltage per sensor for the current psu slot no. 0 in this field tells the psu doesnt support output voltage reading or output voltage read error.

extremePowerSupplyOutputCurrent.name: extremePowerSupplyOutputCurrent
extremePowerSupplyOutputCurrent.description: Output current per sensor for the current psu slot no. 0 in this field tells the psu doesnt support output current reading or output current read error.

extremePowerSupplyOutputUnitMultiplier.name: extremePowerSupplyOutputUnitMultiplier
extremePowerSupplyOutputUnitMultiplier.description: The magnitude of volts and amps for the usage value in extremePowerSupplyOutputVoltage and extremePowerSupplyOutputCurrent.

extremePowerSupplyUsageTable.name: extremePowerSupplyUsageTable
extremePowerSupplyUsageTable.description: The power supply usage on each slot.

extremePowerSupplyUsageEntry.name: extremePowerSupplyUsageEntry
extremePowerSupplyUsageEntry.description: An entry in the power supply usage table.

extremeSlotIndex.name: extremeSlotIndex
extremeSlotIndex.description: Slot number in the chassis/stack based system.

extremePowerSupplyUsageValue.name: extremePowerSupplyUsageValue
extremePowerSupplyUsageValue.description: Power Usage of the particular slot in the chassis or stack.The power usage is measured in milli-watts.

extremePowerSupplyUnitMultiplier.name: extremePowerSupplyUnitMultiplier
extremePowerSupplyUnitMultiplier.description: The magnitude of watts for the usage value in extremePowerSupplyUsageValue.

extremeSystemPowerUsageValue.name: extremeSystemPowerUsageValue
extremeSystemPowerUsageValue.description: The current power usage of the system.In stack mode this variables tells total power usage of the entire system.

extremeSystemPowerUsageUnitMultiplier.name: extremeSystemPowerUsageUnitMultiplier
extremeSystemPowerUsageUnitMultiplier.description: The magnitude of watts for the usage value in extremeSystemPowerUsageValue.

extremeSystemPowerMonitorTable.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorTable
extremeSystemPowerMonitorTable.description: The output power supply table per power supply unit.

extremeSystemPowerMonitorEntry.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorEntry
extremeSystemPowerMonitorEntry.description: An entry in the power supply output table.

extremeSystemPowerMonitorIndex1.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorIndex1
extremeSystemPowerMonitorIndex1.description: Reserved can be used for future expansion. currently set to zero.

extremeSystemPowerMonitorPollInterval.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorPollInterval
extremeSystemPowerMonitorPollInterval.description: Configure how often input power is measured. it is configured in seconds. default value is 60 seconds. if 0 is configured then the input power measurement is disabled

extremeSystemPowerMonitorReportChanges.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorReportChanges
extremeSystemPowerMonitorReportChanges.description: configure report-changes has none or log or trap or log-and-trap, by default none is configured

extremeSystemPowerMonitorChangeThreshold.name: extremeSystemPowerMonitorChangeThreshold
extremeSystemPowerMonitorChangeThreshold.description: configure input power change-threshold to initiate report-changes action. By default 2 watts is configured, this field is configured in watts.

extremeRebootTable.name: extremeRebootTable
extremeRebootTable.description: This group of objects use to initiate a device reboot or contain details of the last reboot operation of the switch modules or nodes.

rebootTimeEntry.name: rebootTimeEntry
rebootTimeEntry.description: This group of objects use to initiate a device reboot or contain details of the last reboot operation of the switch modules or nodes.

extremeRebootSlotId.name: extremeRebootSlotId
extremeRebootSlotId.description: Specifies the MSM/MM module number of a switch or the slot number currently being used by the active stack node.

extremeRebootNodeAddress.name: extremeRebootNodeAddress
extremeRebootNodeAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the SummitStack node to be rebooted. NOTE: This object is valid only for Summit X250e and X450 series switches, and SummitStack.

extremeRebootModuleSlotId.name: extremeRebootModuleSlotId
extremeRebootModuleSlotId.description: Specifies A or B for an MSM/MM module. - A specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot A. - B specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot B. Note: The modules that can be rebooted are management switch fabric modules(MSM) and management modules(MM). This object is valid only on modular switches.

extremeRebootSlotNumber.name: extremeRebootSlotNumber
extremeRebootSlotNumber.description: Specifies the slot number currently being used by the active stack node that is to be rebooted. Note: This variable is available only on SummitStack.

extremeRebootAsStandby.name: extremeRebootAsStandby
extremeRebootAsStandby.description: Specifies that all stack nodes that are to be rebooted are to operate as if configured to not be master-capable. NOTE: This object is valid only for Summit X250e and X450 series switches and SummitStack.

extremeRebootStackTopology.name: extremeRebootStackTopology
extremeRebootStackTopology.description: Specifies that the entire SummitStack is to be rebooted whether or not nodes are active. NOTE: This object is valid only for Summit X250e and X450 series switches and SummitStack.

extremeRebootMonth.name: extremeRebootMonth
extremeRebootMonth.description: Specifies the month that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootDay.name: extremeRebootDay
extremeRebootDay.description: Specifies the day that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootYear.name: extremeRebootYear
extremeRebootYear.description: Specifies the year that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootHour.name: extremeRebootHour
extremeRebootHour.description: Specifies the hour that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootMinute.name: extremeRebootMinute
extremeRebootMinute.description: Specifies the number of minutes that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootSeconds.name: extremeRebootSeconds
extremeRebootSeconds.description: Specifies the number of seconds that the reboot is scheduled to start.

extremeRebootCancel.name: extremeRebootCancel
extremeRebootCancel.description: Cancels a previously scheduled reboot. Note: This object, when enabled, override all objects associated with a reboot request.

extremeRebootImmediate.name: extremeRebootImmediate
extremeRebootImmediate.description: Indicates that a reboot should be executed on the target device immediately.

extremeRebootRowStatus.name: extremeRebootRowStatus
extremeRebootRowStatus.description: The existence state of this reboot request. This object follows the row status behavior.

extremeDownloadImageTable.name: extremeDownloadImageTable
extremeDownloadImageTable.description: This group of objects contain details of the last or the current download image operation of the switch modules or nodes.

extremeDownloadImageEntry.name: extremeDownloadImageEntry
extremeDownloadImageEntry.description: This group of objects contain details of the last or the current download image operation of one of the switch modules or nodes.

extremeDownloadImageSlotId.name: extremeDownloadImageSlotId
extremeDownloadImageSlotId.description: Specifies the MSM/MM module number of a switch or the slot number currently being used by the active stack node.

extremeDownloadImageStatus.name: extremeDownloadImageStatus
extremeDownloadImageStatus.description: Specifies the status of the current down load operation.

extremeDownloadImageFilename.name: extremeDownloadImageFilename
extremeDownloadImageFilename.description: Specifies the file name of the downloading EXOS image.

extremeDownloadImagePartition.name: extremeDownloadImagePartition
extremeDownloadImagePartition.description: Specifies which partition the image should be saved to primary or secondary. Select primary to save the image to the primary partition and secondary to save the image to the secondary partition. Note: Beginning with ExtremeXOS 12.1, an ExtremeXOS core image must be installed on the alternate (nonactive) partition. If a user tries to install on an active partition, the error message [Error: Image can only be installed to the non-active partition.] is displayed.

extremeDownloadImageHostName.name: extremeDownloadImageHostName
extremeDownloadImageHostName.description: Specifies the hostname of the TFTP server from which the image should be obtained.

extremeDownloadImageIpaddress.name: extremeDownloadImageIpaddress
extremeDownloadImageIpaddress.description: Specifies the IP address of the TFTP server from which the image should be obtained.

extremeDownloadImageStartTime.name: extremeDownloadImageStartTime
extremeDownloadImageStartTime.description: Specifies the start time (date and time) of the current down load operation.

extremeDownloadImageMemorycard.name: extremeDownloadImageMemorycard
extremeDownloadImageMemorycard.description: Specifies that the image should be obtained from a removable storage device, which can be a compact flash card or a USB 2.0 storage device.

extremeDownloadImageInstall.name: extremeDownloadImageInstall
extremeDownloadImageInstall.description: Specifies to start the install process after the successful download of the image.

extremeDownloadSlotNumber.name: extremeDownloadSlotNumber
extremeDownloadSlotNumber.description: Specifies the slot number currently being used by the active stack node that is to be rebooted. Note: This variable is available only on stackable switches in a stack.

extremeDownloadModuleSlotId.name: extremeDownloadModuleSlotId
extremeDownloadModuleSlotId.description: Specifies A or B for an MSM/MM module. - A specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot A. - B specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot B. Note: The modules that can be rebooted are management switch fabric modules(MSM) and management modules(MM). This object is valid only on modular switches.

extremeDownloadRowStatus.name: extremeDownloadRowStatus
extremeDownloadRowStatus.description: The existence state of this download image request. This object follows the row status behavior.

extremeInstallImageTable.name: extremeInstallImageTable
extremeInstallImageTable.description: This group of objects contain details of the last or the current install image operation of the switch modules or nodes.

extremeInstallImageEntry.name: extremeInstallImageEntry
extremeInstallImageEntry.description: This group of objects contain details of the last or the current install image operation of one of the switch modules or nodes.

extremeInstallImageSlotId.name: extremeInstallImageSlotId
extremeInstallImageSlotId.description: Specifies the MSM/MM module number of a switch or the slot number currently being used by the active stack node.

extremeInstallImageStatus.name: extremeInstallImageStatus
extremeInstallImageStatus.description: Specifies the status of the current install image operation.

extremeInstallImagePartition.name: extremeInstallImagePartition
extremeInstallImagePartition.description: Specifies which partition the image should be saved to: primary or secondary. Select primary to save the image to the primary partition and secondary to save the image to the secondary partition. Note: Beginning with ExtremeXOS 12.1, an ExtremeXOS core image must be installed on the alternate (nonactive) partition. If a user tries to install on an active partition, the error message [Error: Image can only be installed to the non-active partition.] is displayed.

extremeInstallImageStartTime.name: extremeInstallImageStartTime
extremeInstallImageStartTime.description: Specifies the start time of the current install operation.

extremeInstallImageReboot.name: extremeInstallImageReboot
extremeInstallImageReboot.description: Specifies to reboot the switch after the image is installed.

extremeInstallImageModuleSlotId.name: extremeInstallImageModuleSlotId
extremeInstallImageModuleSlotId.description: Specifies A or B for an MSM/MM module. - A specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot A. - B specifies the MSM/MM installed in slot B. Note: The modules that can be rebooted are management switch fabric modules(MSM) and management modules(MM). This object is valid only on modular switches.

extremeInstallImageSlotNumber.name: extremeInstallImageSlotNumber
extremeInstallImageSlotNumber.description: Specifies the slot number currently being used by the active stack node that is to be rebooted. Note: This variable is available only on stackable switches in a stack.

extremeInstallImageRowStatus.name: extremeInstallImageRowStatus
extremeInstallImageRowStatus.description: The existence state of this install image request. This object follows the row status behavior.

downloadImageTrapEnable.name: downloadImageTrapEnable
downloadImageTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the downloadImageTrap notification. A no(2) value will prevent notifications from being generated by this system.

installImageTrapEnable.name: installImageTrapEnable
installImageTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the extremeInstallImageTrap notification. A no(2) value will prevent notifications from being generated by this system.

downloadImageTrap.name: downloadImageTrap
downloadImageTrap.description: This notification indicates the status of the last/current download operation.

installImageTrap.name: installImageTrap
installImageTrap.description: This notification indicates the status of the last/current install operation.

extremeMasterMSMSlot.name: extremeMasterMSMSlot
extremeMasterMSMSlot.description: The extremeSlotNumber of the master MSM module.

extremeChassisPortsPerSlot.name: extremeChassisPortsPerSlot
extremeChassisPortsPerSlot.description: The maximum number of ports that can be accomodated in a single slot. This number would change to accomodate blades with higher port density than current ones.

extremeSlotTable.name: extremeSlotTable
extremeSlotTable.description: A table containing information about each slot in the chassis.

extremeSlotEntry.name: extremeSlotEntry
extremeSlotEntry.description: A table entry containing information about the module in each slot of the chassis.

extremeSlotNumber.name: extremeSlotNumber
extremeSlotNumber.description: A unique integer identifying the particular slot in the chassis.

extremeSlotName.name: extremeSlotName
extremeSlotName.description: A name identifying the particular slot in the chassis.

extremeSlotModuleConfiguredType.name: extremeSlotModuleConfiguredType
extremeSlotModuleConfiguredType.description: The configured module type for the given slot. At startup, the module-type is none(1). It is possible to configure the module-type even if there is no module in the slot. If the current module in the slot is different than the requested configured module-type, then the current configuration for the module is erased and the card will be restarted. The new configured module-type will be recorded. Since the configured module type is different than the actual module type, a moduleMismatch trap will be sent, and the extremeSlotModuleState for that module will show a mismatch(3). Setting this variable to none(1) will clear the previously assigned module-type of this slot, and all configuration information related to the slot will be erased.

extremeSlotModuleInsertedType.name: extremeSlotModuleInsertedType
extremeSlotModuleInsertedType.description: The module type inserted into the slot. It is possible to have a slot inserted into the slot even though extremeSlotConfiguredType is none(1).

extremeSlotModuleState.name: extremeSlotModuleState
extremeSlotModuleState.description: The state of the module inserted in this slot.

extremeSlotModuleSerialNumber.name: extremeSlotModuleSerialNumber
extremeSlotModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the module inserted in this slot.

extremeHealthCheckErrorType.name: extremeHealthCheckErrorType
extremeHealthCheckErrorType.description: The error reported in the system health check trap

extremeHealthCheckAction.name: extremeHealthCheckAction
extremeHealthCheckAction.description: The action/alarm level configured for health check.

extremeHealthCheckMaxRetries.name: extremeHealthCheckMaxRetries
extremeHealthCheckMaxRetries.description: The maximum number of times a module restart will be attempted if it fails. If extremeHealthCheckAction is not autorecovery(5), then this value is zero.

extremeCpuUtilRisingThreshold.name: extremeCpuUtilRisingThreshold
extremeCpuUtilRisingThreshold.description: Rising threshold for CPU Aggregation utilization trap

extremeCpuTaskUtilPair.name: extremeCpuTaskUtilPair
extremeCpuTaskUtilPair.description: TaskName/CPU_% Util pair reported in CPU Utilization trap

extremeSystemPowerStatus.name: extremeSystemPowerStatus
extremeSystemPowerStatus.description: Change in status of System Power The trap will not be generated for discovering state.

extremeGenericTrap.name: extremeGenericTrap
extremeGenericTrap.description: Some event took place in the system

severity.name: severity
severity.description: The severity of the message being sent.

extremePsuPowerStatus.name: extremePsuPowerStatus
extremePsuPowerStatus.description: Trap to indicate change in status of Power Supply.

extremeSystemPowerUsageNotification.name: extremeSystemPowerUsageNotification
extremeSystemPowerUsageNotification.description: Whenever the power usage is increased/decreased by the configured threshold value then the power usage trap is generated if the trap is enabled..
